The Peoples Democratic Party on Thursday evening announced the closure of all campaign activities for the presidential and national assembly elections. National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba, in a statement said “PDP hereby informs the general public that, in line with the provisions of the Electoral Act 2022, all campaign activities and materials related to our Presidential Candidate, Atiku Abubakar, his running mate, Sen. Dr. Ifeanyi Okowa and our National Assembly Candidates for the Saturday, February 25, 2023 Presidential and National Assembly elections close at midnight today, Thursday, February 23, 2023. “Consequently, the PDP directs all our campaign units, support groups and supporters of our candidates to end all forms of campaign activities accordingly. “The public, particularly the media should take note that our Party and candidates will not be liable for any campaign activity and/or material that appears on any platform after the stipulated time. “The PDP sincerely appreciates Nigerians for the unprecedented outpouring of love, solidarity and support for our Presidential Candidate, Atiku Abubakar, his running mate, Sen. Dr. Ifeanyi Okowa and the National Assembly candidates of our Party throughout the campaign period. “We urge Nigerians to remain at alert and resist any attempt by anybody to subvert their Will at the polls.”